voice_to_text: once with your friend they're on their phone you be like bro why you the textiest right now y'all in the comments y'all the commentiest  have you ever heard a joke and then had the urge to ruin it by being a flippin nerd cause that's what I'm about to do cause I was thinking to myself like why is something like “you're the textiest” funny in a linguistic sense and I think there are two big reasons why the first is that -iest, I E S T, is usually paired with adjectives that end in that /i/ (ee) vowel right like the smelliest is the most smelly the friendliest is the most friendly so when you say some like textiest you're also sneakily implying and established texty and I'm not saying that texty is impossible or unheard of but it's not the most common right so if you say textiest and the other person doesn't have texty in their you know linguistic toolbox right that unexpected nature might turn into humor and related to that nouns that end in that /i/ vowel often represent like diminutives or cute things right think puppy kitty baby Pookie some implying something like texty can also evoke like you know immature childlike cute behaviour and using that /i/ vowel to evoke something more childlike and diminutive and immature that can also get you pretty far in comedy like do you think gritty would be as funny and successful if his name was just grit cause I don't think so and if you can harness the unexpected nature of it all right like going from text to textiest and skipping over “texty” entirely and if you can harness the cute diminutive nature of it all which often happens in words that end in the /i/ vowel I think both of them together they can generate a good amount of laughs

voice_to_text: Overwatch fans should want Marvel rivals to succeed, and if you don't want Marvel rivals to succeed, I don't really think you're a real Overwatch fan. As someone who didn't get lucky enough to get a code on like day one, fingers crossed I can get it somehow. I've been itching to play a new hero. Shoot. But in spite of that, I think this game should be a long ways off from release. Because Overwatch does need a valid competitor in the market, but currently Marvel rivals is not that. The game looks extremely like sluggish and buggy. Which is fine for an alpha test, but I mean we all remember multiverses. Live service games in general, especially free to play new IPS love to try and get their product out as soon as possible to start recouping cost, but in so doing tend to sacrifice the quality of their product in order to get it in the hands of people. To make a quick the developer of this game being Net Ease Games is really concerning. They put out a lot of shovel wear slop for the App Store. And my hope is that they either have something to prove with this game so they're actually gonna put some significant effort behind, or that Marvel is looking for a higher quality assurance bar. Because when your target is to fight with Overwatch, a Blizzard IP, you need to have polish and quality behind your product. You need to Have a thorough, detailed roadmap at launch. And while currently this is an alpha test so it doesn't need to be perfect by any means, my worry is that this company will jump the shark and release a game way too early like a lot of live service products do. But if they can get the polish up, if they can get a significant road map up, if they can launch it in a polished state. Overwatch actually having a competitor again is a huge bonus to the game because it means their devs actually have to start working really hard on making the game better. Not saying that they don't, but I am saying they don't have competition.
